  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.earth_escape.description": "Sink into the earth and travel through soil and stone while greatly increasing movement speed. Consumes 8 qi each second underground and ends upon returning to the surface.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.cleanse.description": "Recite a cleansing incantation to wash over the body, removing all lingering curses, afflictions, and negative effects.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.qi_gathering.description": "Focus solely on absorbing the qi of heaven and earth. While active, you possess no offensive or defensive abilities, and all damage received is tripled.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.lingzhi_bullet.description": "Condense a thread of spiritual power at your fingertip and release it with a light flick. The qi cost is minimal, yet it can wound enemies and shatter up to three blocks of stone.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.wind_blade.description": "Gather fierce winds into a razor-sharp blade. Whether slashing, cutting, or piercing, its edge can grievously wound an enemy.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.wind_step.description": "A movement technique that may be toggled at will. Winds gather beneath your feet, greatly increasing speed and granting an additional midair jump. Consumes 5 qi per second.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.yufeng_jue.description": "Ride the winds and drift through the air at low altitude. Consumes 30 qi per second. If no solid ground exists within twenty meters below, the power of flight is lost.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.smoke_art.description": "Condense mist into a projectile and launch it forward. Those caught within the spreading smoke are blinded and unable to see for ten breaths.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.sliding_water.description": "Launch a condensed water orb that forms a shallow pool upon impact. Those who step into it find their movements distorted and their controls reversed.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.ignite_flare.description": "Channel true fire into a blazing streak that races forward. Grass, wood, stone, and all it touches are set aflame.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.spirit_sight.description": "A spiritual eye technique that may be freely toggled. When active, night appears as bright as day. Consumes 5 qi per second.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.light_beam_attack.description": "Expend 90 qi to summon six hexagonal spirit orbs behind you, stacking up to three layers. A punch fires a single orb, while a concealed strike releases them all at once. Each orb possesses immense destructive power, capable of devastating powerful foes and shattering large areas of terrain.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.dielang_shield.description": "Condense layers of water-aspected spiritual power into protective shields. One layer costs 50 qi and blocks 12 damage; two layers cost 100 qi and block 36 damage; three layers cost 150 qi and withstand 108 damage.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.zhenshan_palm.description": "Gather the power of earth and stone into a colossal palm strike. The palm persists for three breaths, crushing all rock and soil in its path.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.weiya.description": "A pressure aura technique that may be activated at will. Vast cultivation pressure radiates from your body, consuming 10% of your total qi each second while suppressing creatures whose cultivation is below your own.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.absorb_cultivation.description": "Launch a dark-aspected spirit projectile. If it strikes someone with lower cultivation, one-tenth of their cultivation progress is extracted and added to your own.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.tuntian.description": "Devour all earth and stone within a five-meter radius, leaving nothing behind. Each block consumed advances your cultivation. The technique also devastates nearby living beings, and slain foes have their essence absorbed to greatly increase your cultivation.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.fengya.description": "A toggleable secret technique. After channeling power, every punch—whether through the air, against stone, or at an enemy—unleashes a spiraling cone of compressed wind. Upon reaching the Jindan Realm, concealed punches can summon a far larger wind cone.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.dingshen.description": "Silently recite an arcane incantation and launch a metal-aspected spirit projectile. Targets with lower cultivation become rigid and unable to move for a short time.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.yinlei_jue.description": "Commune with the spiritual energies of heaven and earth, launch a lightning talisman, and call down heavenly lightning to strike the target.",
  "spell.immortal_cultivation_mod.wulei_zhengfa.description": "An orthodox Daoist lightning art. Palm lightning and heavenly thunder descend together as five mighty lightning pillars, specializing in the destruction of evil spirits and demonic beings.",
  "method_special.immortal_cultivation_mod.blood_demon": "Cultivating this method refines your own blood essence into Blood Qi. Thereafter, techniques and cultivation arts consume Blood Qi instead of Spiritual Qi.",
  "method_special.immortal_cultivation_mod.reincarnation_true_art": "Upon mastery, you naturally acquire the Absorb technique. Striking those of lower cultivation allows you to seize their cultivation and strengthen your own Dao foundation.",
  "method_special.immortal_cultivation_mod.tuntian_demon_art": "This method grants the divine power of Devouring Heaven, allowing the user to consume earth, stone, and living beings, transforming their essence into cultivation progress.",
  "method_special.immortal_cultivation_mod.pokong_jue": "Mastering this method grants the Wind Pressure technique. Every punch tears through the air with destructive wind cones capable of injuring enemies and shattering stone.",
  "method_special.immortal_cultivation_mod.changqing_jue": "Spiritual qi subtly nourishes the surroundings, causing nearby plants to flourish, though wild weeds and thorns will not grow.",
  "method_special.immortal_cultivation_mod.fentian_life_renewal": "When a cultivator falls for the first time, death does not come immediately. The soul persists as a spirit form for the duration of an incense stick, leaving a trail of flames before reforming the body with a final spark of life. Once the body has fully recovered, this life-saving ability may be used again."
}
